WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
Cambridge English readers. Level 1. Hotel Casanova by Sue Leather.

00:17.000 --> 00:21.000
Hotel Casanova by Sue Leather.

00:30.000 --> 00:35.000
Chapter 1. Dino.

00:36.000 --> 00:43.000
The 20th of April was Dino Braco's 21st birthday. He worked.

00:44.000 --> 00:51.000
Giovanni, his boss at the hotel grand, brought him a cake from the hotel kitchen.

00:51.000 --> 00:58.000
Just 21. Said Giovanni, and he put his hand on Dino's back.

00:59.000 --> 01:04.000
Ah, Dino Dino. When I was 21.

01:05.000 --> 01:17.000
Dino ate some cake and smiled. He was only 21 years old, but he was a young man who knew what he wanted. He had a plan.

01:18.000 --> 01:29.000
You must know what you want, Dino. His mother said to him when he was a child, and he did. He had a plan.

01:30.000 --> 01:44.000
Dino came from a very small town called Rachella in the south of Italy. His mother and father were farmers. Rachella was beautiful, but no one had any money.

01:45.000 --> 01:54.000
Dino was born there, but now he lived and worked in Venice. He worked at the reception of the hotel grand.

01:55.000 --> 01:59.000
Wow! said Dino's friends in Rachella.

02:00.000 --> 02:06.000
You're at a big hotel on the Venice Lido. How did you get that job?

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
Dino smiled.

02:10.000 --> 02:15.000
Because I work hard, he thought, and I have a plan.

02:16.000 --> 02:30.000
Dino liked his work at the reception. When guests came in, he said hello to them, and he asked, Sir, Madam, would you like a glass of suave, one of Venice's famous wines?

02:31.000 --> 02:44.000
He took their credit cards. When they weren't from Italy, he took their passports. Then he asked the boy to take their bags to their room. He helped the guests.

02:45.000 --> 02:53.000
Yes, Madam, of course, Madam. Dino's boss, Giovanni Tardelli, thought he was a good boy.

02:54.000 --> 03:09.000
He knew a girl at the hotel, who also came from Rachella. Her name was Maria Luca, and she worked as a waitress. Maria was nice, and he liked to talk to her, but she was just a friend.

03:10.000 --> 03:16.000
On his birthday, she gave him a small picture of Rachella, their town.

03:17.000 --> 03:24.000
I did it. She smiled at him. You can look at the picture and think about home.

03:25.000 --> 03:39.000
Thank you, Maria. Dino smiled and put the picture in his little room. The picture was nice, but he didn't think about Rachella much. He liked to think about his plans.

03:40.000 --> 03:52.000
Women liked Dino. Well, why not? He was good-looking, with dark, curly hair and beautiful brown eyes. And he was nice.

03:53.000 --> 04:05.000
The women who came to the hotel liked to talk to him. Dino was kind to them. But women were not in Dino's plans, not for the moment.

04:06.000 --> 04:14.000
When I'm 26, he thought, I'm going to meet a woman, the woman I want to marry.

04:15.000 --> 04:34.000
Dino knew that it was important to look good. It was his job. He always wore good clothes, beautiful shirts, nice jackets and trousers. His hair always looked good, and he was always elegante.

04:36.000 --> 04:45.000
He knew that Italy was famous for nice clothes and beautiful things. That's why people came to Italy, to Venice.

04:46.000 --> 05:01.000
Dino worked very long hours, and he didn't make much money. His room, at the back of the hotel, was very small. It just had a small bed, a table and light, and somewhere for his clothes.

05:02.000 --> 05:15.000
But Dino didn't think about the long hours, the little money, and the small room. He liked his job at the hotel grand. And it was only the start. He knew what he wanted.

05:16.000 --> 05:26.000
Every night he wrote about the day in his little black book. Then he looked at his plans. He liked to read them every day.

05:27.000 --> 05:39.000
The night of the 20th of April, his 21st birthday, Dino sat in his little room and looked at his little black book. He looked at his plans.

05:40.000 --> 05:55.000
Everything is good, he thought. But on the 21st of April, something changed his plans. The woman with the long dark hair came and stayed at the hotel grand, and everything changed.

05:57.000 --> 06:04.000
Chapter Two, Dino in Love.

06:06.000 --> 06:14.000
Good morning. My name is Carla Moretti, said the woman. And I have a room.

06:15.000 --> 06:24.000
Dino looked up from his computer. The woman was talking to Beppo, the other young man who worked at the reception.

06:25.000 --> 06:38.000
Dino saw a beautiful woman with brown eyes. She smiled and looked into Dino's eyes. He looked down quickly, but it was too late.

06:39.000 --> 06:50.000
The woman left the reception to go to her room. Again, Dino looked up. The woman was very slim and she wore a beautiful blue jacket.

06:51.000 --> 06:56.000
It was the color of the sky in spring and it looked very expensive.

06:58.000 --> 07:06.000
Do you like her? asked Beppo, laughing. Dino looked down again quickly.

07:07.000 --> 07:11.000
No, I, er, I'm just trying to finish this.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
Beppo laughed again and went into the kitchen.

07:17.000 --> 07:30.000
That evening, Dino was in reception. At about 1130, he heard the telephone. He looked at the room lights. It was room 216.

07:31.000 --> 07:38.000
Carla Moretti's room. He answered the phone. Reception, can I help you, madam?

07:39.000 --> 07:47.000
Yes, said the beautiful voice. I want a sandwich, but room service is not replying.

07:48.000 --> 07:57.000
I can help you, madam, said Dino. Dino phoned room service and asked them to phone room 216.

07:58.000 --> 08:04.000
About 45 minutes later, the woman in room 216 phoned reception again.

08:05.000 --> 08:14.000
I just want to say thank you, said Carla Moretti, and you have a very nice voice.

08:15.000 --> 08:24.000
Dino's face went red. They talked for a minute or two. She lived in Rome, but she loved Venice.

08:25.000 --> 08:31.000
He told her that his name was Dino. They laughed. He thought she was very nice.

08:32.000 --> 08:49.000
The next day, Dino thought about Carla Moretti all the time. At about 430 in the afternoon, she came into the hotel. She had lots of bags from expensive shops. She looked tired after her day of shopping.

08:50.000 --> 08:57.000
She went into the cafe just across from the reception. Dino walked quickly into the cafe.

08:58.000 --> 09:10.000
Carla Moretti asked for a coffee. Dino walked up to the young waiter, took the coffee and said, can I take that? The waiter smiled at Dino.

09:11.000 --> 09:20.000
Your coffee, madam, said Dino. He put the small cup of coffee in front of Carla Moretti. She looked up.

09:21.000 --> 09:31.000
It's the man with the beautiful voice, Dino, she said. She looked at him and he looked into her brown eyes.

09:32.000 --> 09:46.000
Er, your coffee, madam, he smiled. He turned to go, but she took his arm. She pulled him to her until his ear was near her mouth.

09:47.000 --> 09:59.000
This evening, at about 10.30, she said, I'm going to order drinks in my room. Please bring them. Do you understand?

10:00.000 --> 10:02.000
Dino went red.

10:03.000 --> 10:10.000
Er, I... well, yes, madam, he said. Very good, she said.

10:10.000 --> 10:17.000
She picked up the Corriere de la Sera newspaper and started to read it.

10:18.000 --> 10:24.000
Dino went back to the reception and waited. He phoned room service.

10:25.000 --> 10:32.000
When room 216 orders drinks, he said, I want to take them to Signora Moretti's room.

10:33.000 --> 10:39.000
Time went very slowly. Then, at about 10.30, room service phoned.

10:40.000 --> 10:44.000
Dino took Carla Moretti's drinks to her room.

10:45.000 --> 10:51.000
Ah, the man with the beautiful voice, she said, when she opened the door.

10:52.000 --> 10:55.000
Come in. I want to talk to you.

10:55.000 --> 11:02.000
Carla drank whiskey. Dino drank water because he was still at work.

11:03.000 --> 11:09.000
Sit down here, said Carla, and tell me everything about yourself.

11:10.000 --> 11:15.000
Dino never told anyone about his plans, but he told Carla.

11:16.000 --> 11:20.000
He talked to her about his plan to marry when he was 26.

11:20.000 --> 11:29.000
And then, when I'm 30 years old, I want my own hotel with my name over the door, he said.

11:30.000 --> 11:33.000
I want it more than anything in the world.

11:34.000 --> 11:42.000
Carla listened. Her eyes didn't leave Dino's face. His face was red. He felt hot.

11:43.000 --> 11:47.000
Hotel Casanova, he finished.

11:48.000 --> 12:00.000
How wonderful, she said. Hotel Casanova, what a beautiful plan, and you are very nice.

12:01.000 --> 12:10.000
She put her hand on his hot face and pulled him towards her. She kissed him. He kissed her.

12:10.000 --> 12:19.000
Dino kissed girls back home in Rachella, but their kisses weren't like Carla's kisses.

12:20.000 --> 12:28.000
That night, Dino didn't sleep in his little room. He slept with Carla Marretti in room 216.

12:29.000 --> 12:33.000
At five o'clock in the morning, Dino opened his eyes.

12:33.000 --> 12:44.000
Oh no, he thought. I'm in love. I'm not 26. I'm just 21 years old, and I'm in love.

